Hennessey, Respondent, v. Metropolitan El. Ry. Co. et al., Appellants. (Superior Court of New York City, General Term. March 3, 1891.) Appeal from equity term. Action by James Hennessey against the Metropolitan Elevated Railway Company and others. From a judgment for plaintiff, defendants appeal.

Argued before Truax and Dugro, JJ.

Davies & Rapallo, for appellants. L. C. Dessar, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Judgment affirmed, with costs.
